      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEKTRA ROGER (6) was in winning form two back (23.25) at this track but ran below best last time at Ballarat, finishing 6th. Can make amends. PAW QUEBEC (2) was well supported last time but could only manage third (22.69), beaten one length. Form from his last run is proving strong. Well placed and gets his chance. PAW HARKONNEN (1) stalked the lead but wound up strongly to score (22.06) at Shepparton in Grade 5 over 390m. Has a strong record from this draw, notching two wins and three minor placings from five starts. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. RIGHTEOUS FURY (8) pinged the lids and wasn't headed last time. Right in the mix again.",
